<title type="html"><![CDATA[Animated transformers button.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5164&amp;p=22251#p22251"><![CDATA[
Transformers animated cartoon button.<br /><br />This is more or less, a test, to learn how to use a gif.<br />I followed what Jcee mentioned months ago.<br />&quot;Download a gif, rip, and delete the background. Expect roughness&quot;.<br /><br />There are more low quality gifs, than high quality ones, out there. <br />Guess, because they were invented back in the 80s, when internet bandwidth was small.<br />This is from a low quality cartoon, animated gif.<br />It's the first one that showed up in search.<br />I used &quot;Animated GIF Frame Extractor&quot;, then used &quot;PixelFormer&quot;, to assemble the frames in a vertical column, <br />with one pixel line added to top. <br />That was the easy part.<br />The chore was manually getting rid of the noisy dithered background.<br /><br />If you want to use it,<br />Keep button size under 120<br />Put in check for align to corner.<br /><br /><br /><br />Oh well, I think I just wasted my time. <br />I just found out that someone else already removed the background on a similar gif, on internet. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /> <br />Should have gone for a good quality moving Transformers logo instead.<br /><br /><br />EDIT: Replaced picture with gif made from my animated CSM button.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> â€” Wed Sep 16, 2015 2:27 am</p><hr />
